<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Nineteenth session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
</b></p>
<p><b>political, economic, social and cultural rights,  
</b></p>
<p><b>including the right to development</b> 
</p>
<p><b>  Annual report of the Special Representative of the 
Secretary-General on Violence against Children</b>* **<b> 
</b></p>
<p><i>Summary 
</i></p>
<p> The third report of the Special Representative of the Secretary-General on Violence 
against Children is submitted to the Council in accordance with General Assembly 
resolution 65/197. 
</p>
<p> The report reviews key developments and initiatives promoted, and identifies 
priority areas to which the Special Representative will devote special attention to accelerate 
progress in children&#8216;s protection from all forms of violence. 
</p>
<p> 
 
</p>
<p>  
 * Late submission. 
 ** The annex to the present report is being circulated as received, in the language of submission only. 
</p>

